## 39. Index Funds
**Definition**: Investment funds that track a specific market index.

**Example**: 
**Vanguard S&P 500 Index Fund (VFIAX)**:
- Tracks the S&P 500 index
- Automatically holds all 500 companies in the same proportions as the index
- If Apple is 7% of the S&P 500, then 7% of the fund is in Apple
- Expense ratio: 0.04% (very low cost)
- Returns match the S&P 500 (minus tiny fees)

You invest $10,000. The fund automatically distributes it across all 500 companies. You get instant diversification. When the S&P 500 rises 10%, so does your investment.

