## 48. Mutual Funds
**Definition**: Pools of money from many investors used to buy a diversified portfolio of securities.

**Example**: 
**Fidelity Contrafund**:
- You invest $5,000
- Your money is pooled with millions from other investors (total fund: $100 billion)
- Professional fund managers use the pool to buy stocks in Meta, Amazon, Microsoft, etc.
- You own a proportional share of all these holdings
- Fund charges 0.85% expense ratio
- You can only buy/sell once per day at closing price (unlike ETFs that trade all day)

Mutual funds are actively managed (managers pick stocks) or passive (track an index).

